{"lemma":"فَمٌ","slug":"فَمٌ","root":"ف.م.م","root_slug":"ف-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-م-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34609"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mouth","examples":[{"text":"يُرِيدُونَ أَن يُطْفِئُوا نُورَ اللَّهِ بِأَفْوَاهِهِمْ"},{"text":"وَالَّذِينَ يَدْعُونَ مِن دُونِهِ لَا يَسْتَجِيبُونَ لَهُم بِشَيْءٍ إِلَّا كَبَاسِطِ كَفَّيْهِ إِلَى الْمَاءِ لِيَبْلُغَ فَاهُ وَمَا هُوَ بِبَالِغِهِ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"muzzle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"orifice, aperture, hole, vent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mouth (of a river), rivermouth"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mouthpiece (of pipe or cigarette), cigarette holder","examples":[{"text":"آلَةُ الْفَمِ","english":"wind instrument"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *pay-."},"ipa":["/fam/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34609","headword_ar":"فَمٌ","root":"fm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mouth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, KL, &c.:) it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawahN","text_ar":"فَوَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, and Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fwh","text_ar":"فوه"},{"kind":"text","text":",) with two fet-hahs, (Msb in that art.,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawohN","text_ar":"فَوْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (so in some copies of the S;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"being cut off from it, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not susceptible of declension, because it is quiescent, therefore"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"is substituted for it; but when you form the dim. or the pl., you restore it to its original state, saying [in the former case]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwayohN","text_ar":"فُوَيْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [in the latter case]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afowaAhN","text_ar":"اَفْوَاهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afomaA='N","text_ar":"اَفْمَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in some of the copies of the S not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afomaAmN","text_ar":"اَفْمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but when you form the rel. n., you say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famiY~N","text_ar":"فَمِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and, if you will, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famawiY~N","text_ar":"فَمَوِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", combining the substitute and the letter for which it is substituted, like as they say in the dual"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famawaAni","text_ar":"فَمَوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; this being held to be allowable because of there being therein another letter rejected, i. e. the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though they made the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this case to be a substitute for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":", not for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) and one says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famayaAni","text_ar":"فَمَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famawaAni","text_ar":"فَمَوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is anomalous; (IAar, K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fwh","text_ar":"فوه"},{"kind":"text","text":";) but one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famaAni","text_ar":"فَمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famawaAni","text_ar":"فَمَوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fwh","text_ar":"فوه"},{"kind":"text","text":":) it has three forms,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famN","text_ar":"فَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fumN","text_ar":"فُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fimN","text_ar":"فِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K, TA:) and some decline it doubly; saying in the nom. case"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fumN","text_ar":"فُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accus."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famFA","text_ar":"فَمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and gen."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fimK","text_ar":"فِمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aimoruw^N","text_ar":"اِمْرُوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonumN","text_ar":"اِبْنُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which have been said to be the only other instances of the kind: (TA:) when it is prefixed to the [pronominal]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY~a","text_ar":"فِىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famiY","text_ar":"فَمِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": but when to [a pronoun] other than the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is declined with the letters"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", so that one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwuhu","text_ar":"فُوُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAhu","text_ar":"فَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi","text_ar":"فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but one also says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famuhu","text_ar":"فَمُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fwh","text_ar":"فوه"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and sometimes the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"is musheddedeh, (S, K,) in poetry, as in the saying, (S, TA,) of Mohammad Ibn-Dhu-eyb El-'Ománee El-Fukeymee, the rájiz, (TA in this art. and in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tsm","text_ar":"طسم"},{"kind":"text","text":",) addressing Er-Rasheed, or, accord. to IKh, said in relation to Suleymán Ibn-'Abd-El-Melik and 'Abd-El- 'Azeez. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tsm","text_ar":"طسم"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yaA layotahaA qado xarajato mino fum~ihi\n                      \n                     \n                        Hat~aY yaEuwda Almuloku fiY A^usoTum~ihi"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uTosum~ihi","text_ar":"اُطْسُمِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O, would that it had gone forth from his mouth, so that the dominion might return"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to its rightful owner;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sTm","text_ar":"سطم"},{"kind":"text","text":", and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tsm","text_ar":"طسم"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and it would have been allowable, (S, TA,) accord. to ISk, (S,) or accord. to Fr, (TA,) if he had said ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn fam~ihi","text_ar":"من فَمِّهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fm","text_ar":"فم"},{"kind":"text","text":", with teshdeed, is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afomaAmN","text_ar":"اَفْمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and its dim. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fumayomN","text_ar":"فُمَيْمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned by Lh. (TA.) MF says that many of the expositors of the Tes-heel have collected the dial. vars. of this word, compounded and uncompounded, and they have exceeded twenty; that with fet-h, they say, being the most common and the most chaste. (TA.) [See more in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fwh","text_ar":"فوه"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfm","text_ar":"الفم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is metonymically applied to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The teeth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 242.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famu AlHuwti","text_ar":"فَمُ الحُوتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The star"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the mouth of Piscis Australis."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw &c.: see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hwt","text_ar":"حوت"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famu Alfarasi","text_ar":"فَمُ الفَرَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The star"},{"kind":"text","text":"[e]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the lip of Pegasus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw.) ―         -b4-  [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famuAlr~aHimi","text_ar":"فَمُالرَّحِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mouth of the womb."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famu Aln~ahori","text_ar":"فَمُ النَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mouth of the river."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA.) ―         -b6-  And [hence likewise,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famN","text_ar":"فَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Branch;"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotN","text_ar":"اِسْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ root. ” (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sth","text_ar":"سته"},{"kind":"text","text":"; in which see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotN","text_ar":"اِسْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last quarter.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famN mina","text_ar":"فَمٌ مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ibaAgi","text_ar":"الدِّبَاغِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantity that is used at one time, of tan;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, K, * TA;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosN minohu","text_ar":"نَفْسٌ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Fr, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}